Interface Paradigmatic

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Context<T>, Exertion, StrategyContext
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AltMogram, ArrayContext, Block, CompoundExertion, ConditionalMogram, ContextResult, ControlContext, CustomContext, DataContext, EvaluationTask, Job, ListContext, LoopMogram, MapContext, ModelerNetTask, ModelerObjectTask, ModelTask, NetBlock, NetJob, NetTask, ObjectBlock, ObjectJob, ObjectTask, OptMogram, PositionalContext, ProcModel, ProviderSession, ScopeContext, ServiceContext, ServiceExertion, SharedAssociativeContext, SharedIndexedContext, SignedServiceTask, SrvModel, Task

    public interface Paradigmatic
    A Paradigm instance can return exact data or evaluated (reevaluated - of Evaluation type). If isModeling is true that returned values of the Evaluation type are evaluated, otherwise returned as is.
